(enablePrefetching, numRCQEntries).explanation: Prefetching is a cache optimization technique while RCQ entries are part of the memory controller's request handling queue, and these operate at different levels of the memory hierarchy without direct causal influence;

(enablePrefetching, flush).explanation: Enabling prefetching can increase the likelihood of pipeline flushes when prefetched data turns out to be incorrect or when prefetching interferes with the processor's branch prediction accuracy;

(enablePrefetching, nICacheTLBWays).explanation: Prefetching functionality and the number of instruction cache TLB ways are independent architectural parameters that operate at different levels of the memory hierarchy;
